  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments used when creating a customized instance of a typeface.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` describes the customization applied when cloning or
instantiating a typeface: the index within a font collection, the active
color palette, per-color overrides, and variation axis positions.

Pass an `SKFontArguments` to <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>
to obtain a typeface customized with these arguments.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    CollectionIndex = 0,
    PaletteIndex = 1,
};
using var typeface = SKTypeface.FromFile("NotoColorEmoji.ttf");
using var custom = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
